the arrests were made march 9-14 in three northeastern provinces, said maj. praphan suvannamajo, an internal security operations command spokesman
the impoverished northeast was once the stronghold of the communists, who fielded about 12,000 fighters at the peak of power in the late 1970s
a government amnesty offer and military raids have crippled the insurgency, and the army says just a few hundred guerrillas remain
the financially troubled de laurentiis entertainment group inc. has agreed to sell the foreign tv, video and non-theatrical rights to virtually its entire 320-movie library for $69 million
the foreign rights are being acquired by a newly formed united kingdom company controlled by financier michael w. stevens, the de laurentiis company said tuesday
the sale will pay off $57 million in bank debt and provide capital for the company, which posted a $36.2 million loss in the first nine months of the last fiscal year
the company's founder, italian filmmaker dino de laurentiis, 68, stepped down as chairman and chief executive last month. the company still seeks a buyer for remaining library rights and its vast wilmington, n.c., studio
the cat's out of the bag. fustuce ringgenberg, better known as fred, proud recipient of a letter offering him a mastercard from an ohio bank with a $5,000 limit, hasn't worked a lick in his 2{ years
janet ringgenberg said she was flabbergasted that her cat got a pre-approved invitation. ms. ringgenberg said she has been trying unsuccessfully to get a credit card since she was divorced three years ago
where's he going to go with it?'' she asked. ``he doesn't even leave home, let alone leave home without it,'' she said with a smirk. ``it's hilarious. i think it's just a big joke.''
fustuce mostly lies on the rug or nestles in the easy chair, she said. his biggest worry is whether he'll get canned tuna
the story probably began a year ago, when ringgenberg's 18-year-old daughter, barbara, filled out a questionnaire on toothpaste and breakfast cereal and mailed it in with fustuce's name on it
i thought they'd send us some free coupons or something,'' ms. ringgenberg said. instead, fustuce's name apparently ended up on a mailing list bought by credit card service bureau of springfield, va., to solicit customers
betty rothgeb, administrative assistant to the company's chairman, said household pets get on the list of prospective customers ``from time to time.''
there's no danger he (fustuce) is going to be given a credit card,'' ms. rothgeb said. ``obviously, since the cat has no credit, it would be denied.''
creditors in vermont cannot take a person's two-horse wagon, pew in church, lettered gravestone or year's worth of yarn in personal bankruptcy proceedings
cars, refrigerators and other items considered modern necessities, however, are not protected by law from creditors. a bill under consideration in the state senate would add those modern inventions and eliminate antiquated items from the list of protected property
the bill received preliminary approval tuesday
there was a judicial case that said sorry, a car is not an ox cart,'' said kirby scarborough, chairman of the vermont bar association's bankruptcy committee, which unanimously endorsed the revision. ``let me ask you something, who has an ox cart these days?''
state archivist gregory sanford said the legislature responded to changing state economies, adding an exemption for sheep in 1811 and for bees and honey in 1850, but the list went unchanged for most of this century
indian soldiers shot and killed at least 24 tamil rebels during search operations in two northeastern districts, a sri lankan military official said today
the official, who cannot be identified under briefing rules, said the operations in the mullaitivu and kilinochchi districts began early tuesday and lasted the entire day. he said eight of those killed were women and that at least four rebels were injured
more than 300 indian soldiers backed by helicopter gunships and tanks were involved in the operation, the official said
the search operations follow the killing of members of the majority sinhalese community, allegedly by the rebels, in neighbouring trincomalee district and retaliatory killings of tamils by an outlawed sinhalese group. at least 98 people have died in trincomalee in the past two weeks
the official said the indians also had searched unsuccessfully for members of the people's liberation group, an ultra-nationalist sinhalese organization
at least 50,000 indian soldiers are in sri lanka to disarm tamil rebels, who have been waging a separatist guerilla war since 1983. the indians were deployed under a peace accord which granted limited autonomy to the minority tamils in exchange for an arms surrender
but the tamils renounced the july 29 accord last fall and since then they have been battling the indian soldiers
the people's liberation front also opposes the peace accord, saying it grants too many concessions to the tamils
india says more than 400 soldiers and at least 1,100 rebels have died in the fighting, but the militants claim that most of the tamils killed were civilians
tamils form 18 percent of sri lanka's 16 million people while the sinhalese comprise 75 percent. tamils say they are discriminated against by the sinhalese, who control the army and the government in sri lanka. control, no evacuations appear necessary, coast guard now says 707 aboard, sted about 1,000; picks up last graf.</note>
an engine fire broke out early today on a cruise ship carrying more than 700 people in the gulf of mexico, but the blaze appeared to have been brought under control, according to officials and a nearby ship's captain
no injuries were reported, said petty officer brian lincoln, of the u.s. coast guard's miami office
the scandinavian star was about 35 miles off isla mujeres, a mexican island north of the tourist resort cancun in the yucatan peninsula, said coast guard lt. jim mazzonna in miami
all we know is that the ship's captain ... is completely out of fire-fighting equipment and has requested additional fire-fighting equipment such as foam, water and co2,'' said lincoln, referring to carbon dioxide
coast guard cutters, the canada star cruise ship and the vessel vera cruz stood by to assist in evacuating passengers, lincoln said
