some israelis are protesting that domestic and foreign journalists covering riots in the occupied lands are producing reports that are pro-palestinian and damaging to israel's image
israel television has received dozens of threatening letters for its reporting of the more than three months of violent protests in the west bank and gaza strip _ coverage most foreign journalists consider mild
even new york mayor edward koch has joined in the criticism. koch wrote in the jersualem post today that television cameras should be barred from the occupied territories
many other nations throughout the world are experiencing troubles similar to those now taking place in israel. should israel be the only nation to allow full television coverage of these troubles?'' koch wrote
an american television network says threats have forced it to hire private guards to protect its offices and an israeli cameraman
there's an escalation in statements against us,'' eli fassman, head of the union of television crews, told israel radio this week. ``these criticisms border on incitement to murder.''
there is also growing physical danger in covering the rioting, the managing director of israel's state-run television, chaim yavin, said in an interview
he said israel television cameramen have been given a special first aid and self-protection course. they were taught to defend themselves against a mob, make speedy exits and use the camera as a weapon, the daily hadashot reported
in the occupied west bank's al amari camp, cameramen were seen tuesday wearing large tin containers over their heads to protect themselves from stones
most of the mail that arrives at israel television is critical
we are accused of being leftists, plo supporters. there are threatening letters, too,'' said yavin
an israel television spokeswoman, sari timmerman, said at least five or six such letters arrive each day at her office while others go directly to yavin
the number of letters has not increased since the anti-occupation rioting began dec. 8, but most are now devoted to patriotic criticism of israel television's performance in the west bank and gaza strip
many ask why we permit hostile elements to use state-run media for expressing their views,'' ms. timmerman said
there are also telephoned complaints
if the action gets tough, we get up to 100 calls a night, most from people who say they don't want to see this or want us to be more favorable to the government,'' said yair stern, the head of the news department
the tv's arab-language department faces another kind of threat
israeli media reports said its workers have received palestine liberation organization-inspired calls to stop cooperating with israeli authorities and resign. department head yosef barel denied the reports
people in the territories want coverage, and they know no arab tv is covering them apart from us,'' he said
foreign networks are sometimes accused of inflaming violence and unwittingly aiding anti-israeli rioters
the press _ and i'm speaking primarily about the foreign tv networks _ has explicitly been a side involved in the events,'' president chaim herzog has said. he said foreign television crews are ``the main weapon'' of the arabs
he was the latest in a series of israeli officials to criticize foreign media. prime minister yitzhak shamir, defense minister yitzhak rabin and army spokesman brig. gen. ephraim lapid also have spoken out
