it turned out that it was the tipster who was tipsy. the motorist failed a sobriety test and was arrested for investigation of drunken driving, taylor said
the truck was probably going straight, and he was the one weaving,'' taylor added
multiple births increased slightly in the united states from 1984 to 1985, according to insurance company figures issued wednesday
multiple births were up 6 percent during the period _ although they still accounted for only 2.1 percent of the 3.7 million recorded live births, according to the statistical bulletin, a quarterly publication produced by the metropolitan life insurance co
most of the multiple births were twins. however, fertility drugs have slightly increased the odds for triplets, the report said. in 1985, 2.5 percent of multiple births involved three or more babies _ up from 2.1 percent in 1983
