authorities say seven guards, one prison cook and an inmate were charged as a result of ``operation ferret,'' an investigation begun 18 months ago
the investigation will potentially yield the largest number of arrests related to official misconduct by correctional officers in this country's history,'' district attorney ronald castille told a news conference tuesday
