that too may pass without much disruption of stock prices, brokers say, but until it is over it adds an additional element of uncertainty for investors. drops</head>
warner-lambert co. said it is planning a $5 million joint venture with the people's republic of china to make and market chewing gum, cough drops and candies
the pharmaceutical company said an agreement with the chinese government calls for a plant to be built in the city of harbin, capital of the northeastern province heilongjang
warner-lambert said it would provide the machinery and technology while the government would provide the land, building and some equipment
the joint venture, to be called the harbin warner-lambert confectionary co. ltd., would employ about 120 people, the company said in an announcement tuesday. the plant would produce dentyne gum, halls cough drops and fruitfuls candies for use in china and for export
warner-lambert has another joint partnership with china, called suzhou capsugel ltd., which makes empty hard gelatin capsules. it was established in 1985
