de laurentiis still is seeking a buyer for the remaining rights to its library and the sprawling wilmington, n.c., studio where most of its films are made
the company has been dogged by a string of box-office flops since it went public three years ago
in first nine months of the company's past fiscal year, it took $42.5 million in writeoffs on unsuccessful films. the company posted a net loss for the three quarters of $36.2 million. results of the fiscal year ended feb. 29 haven't been released
